Nite Owl sighed. "I don't know, Rorschach. I feel...empty."
I raised an eyebrow. "Empty? After everything we've been through together?"
He nodded. "Yeah. It just feels like...there's something missing. Like I'm not making a difference."
I chuckled. "Don't be silly, Ollie. We're making a difference every day. We're keeping watch over this city, protecting innocent people from the villains."
"I know," he said, his voice soft. "It's just hard sometimes. To see the evil in the world, and know that there's nothing you can do to stop it."
I sighed. "I know what you mean. But we have to keep fighting, even when it's hard. Because that's what heroes do. That's what we were trained to do."
Nite Owl looked at me, his eyes shining with determination. "You're right, Rorschach. We can't give up now. We have to keep moving forward, no matter what."
I smiled. "You got it, partner. Let's get back to work."
We turned and walked away, ready to take on whatever challenges lay ahead. We may be two mismatched individuals, but together, we make a formidable team.」
